# Art and Prefab Conventions

## Visual Identity

Insect Wars is set at **insect scale** on natural ground. Everything is organic — no metal, plastic, or man-made materials. A 3 cm pebble is a 3-story boulder. A grass blade is a 20 m tree. Water droplets are lakes.

- **Art style:** Semi-stylized / toon with soft gradients and muted earth tones
- **Camera:** Top-down RTS at 30–60 m altitude — all art must be readable from above
- **Color pops:** Reserved for game-critical features (team colors, resource nodes, danger zones)
- **No glowing/emissive effects** — use material properties (smoothness, color) for visual distinction

## Scale Reference

- An insect unit is roughly **0.5–1.1 m** tall in Unity units
- Terrain features with `radius = 5` cover ~10 m diameter

## Prefab Rules

- **Pivot** at ground level, center XZ
- **No colliders** — added programmatically by the system
- **No NavMeshObstacle/NavMeshModifier** — added by code
- **No MonoBehaviour scripts** on prefabs
- **No lights or cameras**
- **Y rotation** is set by the system from data — don't bake rotation
- **Not scaled by the system** — model at 1:1 for radius = 1

## Performance Budgets

- Each terrain feature prefab: **under 1500 triangles**
- **1–2 materials** per prefab (URP/Lit or URP/Simple Lit)
- Avoid transparency where possible (use alpha-clip if needed)
- No real-time lights, reflections, or heavy transparency
- Use LODs for complex meshes (rocky ridges)

## Visual Library

All prefabs are assigned via `UnitVisualLibrary` (ScriptableObject). The runtime falls back to **procedural placeholder geometry** when no prefab is provided — this is intentional and expected during development.

## Team Colors

`TeamPalette` provides blue (Player) vs red (Enemy) shell/accent colors. Unit visuals use material tint caching (`Dictionary<Color, Material>`) to avoid runtime instantiation.

## Minimap

Uses an **orthographic RenderTexture camera**. Top-down footprint of all features must be visually distinct and color-coded. Optional `InsectWars/MinimapFog` material overlays fog of war.
